==============================
A hedge is a strategy used to reduce the risk of loss on an investment. This can be done by taking an offsetting position in another asset, such as a futures contract or an option. For example, if you are long bitcoin, you could hedge your position by shorting bitcoin futures. This would protect you from losses if the price of bitcoin falls.

If you shorted with our signals earlier, you sholud be in profit despite the small loss, especially if you used low margin which we recommend.
